
---


@startuml

' Classes

class Sensor {
    +String vendorId
    +String description
    +Unit unit
    +Room room
    +List<Measurement> measurements
    +float getLastValue()
}

abstract class AbstractSensor {
    +String vendorId
    +String description
    +Unit unit
    +Room room
    +List<Measurement> measurements
}

class TemperatureSensor {
    -float min
    -float max
}

class PowerSensor {
    -float totalConsumption
}

class Measurement {
    +Timestamp timestamp
    +float value
}

class Room {
    +String description
    +Apartment apartment
}

class Apartment {
    +Address address
    +List<Room> rooms
    +List<Inhabitant> inhabitants
    +String email
}

class Inhabitant {
    +String username
    +String password
    +Apartment apartment
    +boolean isAdmin
}

class SensorController {
    +Apartment apartment
    +List<Sensor> sensors
    +Map<String, Threshold> thresholds
    +login(username: String, password: String): boolean
    +querySensor(sensorId: String): List<Measurement>
    +getLastValue(sensorId: String): float
    +setThreshold(sensorId: String, threshold: float)
}

class Threshold {
    +float value
    +Sensor sensor
}

class EMonitor {
    +checkThresholds(): void
    +sendAlert(email: String, message: String): void
}

' Interfaces

interface Unit {
    +String getSymbol()
}

enum UnitType implements Unit {
    CELSIUS
    WATT
}

' Relationships

AbstractSensor <|-- TemperatureSensor
AbstractSensor <|-- PowerSensor
Sensor <|-- AbstractSensor

Sensor "1" -- "1" Room : assigned to
Room "1" -- "*" Sensor : contains
Room "1" -- "1" Apartment : part of

Apartment "1" -- "*" Inhabitant : has
Inhabitant "1" -- "1" Apartment : belongs to
Apartment "1" -- "1" SensorController : uses
SensorController "1" -- "*" Sensor : controls
SensorController "1" -- "*" Threshold : maintains

Sensor "1" -- "*" Measurement : has
Measurement "1" -- "1" Sensor : belongs to

EMonitor ..> SensorController : uses
EMonitor ..> Apartment : sends alerts to

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:

- **Sensor** is an abstract class with two concrete types: `TemperatureSensor` and `PowerSensor`.
- Each **Sensor** has a unique `vendorId`, a `description`, and is associated with one **Room**.
- A **Room** can belong to only one **Apartment**, but each **Apartment** can have multiple **Rooms**.
- **Inhabitants** are linked to an **Apartment**, and one can be marked as an **Admin** to perform configuration tasks.
- The **SensorController** handles authentication, querying data, and setting thresholds.
- **EMonitor** is an external system that checks thresholds and sends alerts via the **SensorController** if configured.

